---
// [10] Governance — the Council. Governed by a standards body, not an issuer.
---

<section class="section governance" id="governance" aria-labelledby="governance-heading">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">The Council</p>
    <h2 class="display display--lg reveal" id="governance-heading" data-reveal-delay="0.05">
      Governed by a standards body, not a single issuer.
    </h2>
    <div class="governance__body reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.1">
      <p>
        The Global Gold Council is a Wyoming Decentralized Unincorporated
        Nonprofit Association under Wyo. Stat. § 17-32: a non-profit,
        multi-stakeholder standards body governing the Global Gold protocol.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Council adopts Protocol Standards for eligible collateral,
        participating vaults, approved providers, Standard Metal Units, and
        network governance.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="governance__closer reveal" data-reveal-delay="0.13">
      No single issuer. No single operator. No single hub.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .governance h2 { margin-top: 0.5em; }
  .governance__body {
    margin-top: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.1em;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .governance__body p { margin: 0; }
  .governance__closer {
    margin: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px) 0 0;
    font-family: var(--sans-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold-deep);
  }
</style>
